The paper presents a novel online ensemble learning strategy for portfolio selection, which involves controlling and exploiting a set of commission-oblivious portfolio selection algorithms while handling transaction costs using a commission avoidance mechanism. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories, as it involves developing a new learning strategy for a specific application domain. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the regret bound of the proposed strategy, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves numerical examples to validate the proposed method, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category.
